General.Name: Lord Resources Ltd
General.Description: Lord Resources Limited focuses on the exploration and development of mineral resource projects in Western Australia. The company explores for gold and base metal deposits. The company holds interest in the Cambridge project with two granted exploration licenses covering a total area of 12.1 square kilometers; the Jarama gold project with a single granted exploration license covering an area of 18 square kilometers; the Gabyon gold project with a single granted exploration license covering an area of 33.2 square kilometers; and the Viper polymetallic project with a single granted exploration license covering an area of 3.22 square kilometers located in Western Australia. It intends to acquire a 100% interest in the Horse Rocks polymetallic project with an exploration license application covering an area of 23.8 square kilometers. Lord Resources Limited was formerly known as ENEABBA GAS LIMITED. The company was incorporated in 2003 and is based in West Perth, Australia.
